## Reguired file paths:

/sbin/init ............................ Required by kernel, executes s6-linux-init with arguments
/sbin/init-safemode.................... Optional. Used by kernel to execute s6-linux-init to boot system into 'safemode'
/etc/s6/s6.conf ....................... Configuration for the boot scripts
/etc/s6/zram.conf ..................... Configuration for a zRAM device
/etc/s6/sh-scripts/common_funcs.sh .... Common script fuctions for boot scripts written in sh
/sbin/mkinitramfs ..................... Creates initramfs.img
/sbin/ifup ............................ Brings up network interfaces
/sbin/ifdown .......................... Brings down network interfaces
/usr/share/mkinitramfs/init.in ........ config for mkinitramfs

## Required directories:

/etc/s6/db ............................ Compiled databases for booting
/etc/s6/sh-scripts .................... Required scripts used by the compiled databases in /etc/s6/db
/var/log/dmesg ........................ Owned by s6log user. Stores logged boots by dmesg
/etc/sysconfig/ifconfig.* ............. To setup network interfaces during boot
/lib/services ......................... Helper scripts for ifup/ifdown
